**AI Layer Refactoring — Summary**

**Architecture changes:**
- Flat `packages/ai/src/` with 5 monolithic files → modular structure with 7 subdirectories (29 files total)

**Modules created:**
- `client/` — centralized `callAI()` and `createAIClient()` factory; all HTTP communication goes through one path
- `adapters/` — `AIAdapter` interface + `OpenAIAdapter` implementation; supports custom base URL, model, API key, temperature, max tokens, and `testConnection()`
- `prompts/` — per-domain prompt builders with versioning (`explain.ts`, `vocabulary.ts`, `article.ts`, `video.ts`, `dictionary.ts`); prompts are no longer inline in HTTP-calling code
- `schemas/` — all Zod schemas moved from service files into dedicated per-domain modules; exported types alongside schemas
- `services/` — thin business logic layer that composes client + prompts + schemas; no raw `fetch` calls outside the client
- `errors/` — `AIError` hierarchy: `AIAuthError`, `AIRateLimitError`, `AINetworkError`, `AIEmptyResponseError`, `AIConfigError`
- `utils/` — `AiCache` (generic TTL cache), `extractJSON()`, `parseAndValidate()` helper

**Design patterns applied:**
- **Adapter Pattern** — `AIAdapter` interface decouples the client from provider implementations
- **Strategy Pattern** — pluggable adapters (OpenAI now, others later)
